                             =============
                             datenstrahler
                             =============


This program displays a web site. It's meant to be used in "information
radiators" or similar applications: You create a simple web site that
displays some useful information and then you use datenstrahler on a
small computer with a large screen to display that web site.


Installation
------------

The following C libraries are required:

    - GLib
    - GTK+ 3
    - WebKit2GTK+

datenstrahler expects to be run on a POSIX-ish operating system.

You can customize the program by creating your own config.h based on
config.def.h. In any case, config.h must exist in order to build the
program.

To build the program and install it to /usr/local:

    $ make
    # make install


Running
-------

You usually run the program from a script or terminal:

    $ datenstrahler http://my.website.example.com

Refer to the manpage for all options.
